    of Evil Exidy aka &quot;The Crazy Cracker&quot; and his Apple // computer.</font></p>
  <p><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Courier New, Courier, mono">_______________________________________________________</font></p>
  <p align="left"><font face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="2">] Introduction:</font></p>
  <p align="left"><font size="2" face="Courier New, Courier, mono">] Our first 
    experience with a computer was with an Apple ][ Computer system - as early 
    as 1979, 1980. </font></p>
  <p align="left"><font face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="2">] In 1982 our 
    father would reserve an one hour slot every friday night at the Boulder library 
    (in Boulder Colorado) so we could play on their Apple ][ computers, this was 
    a day both my brother and I would look forward to every week. Aside from playing 
    games at the Arcade and Pong at home, the Apple ][ opened up a totally different 
    door for us - we were now able to copy games from friends and other people 
    in the area using copy programs, one of our favorites was COPY ][ PLUS. Around 
    this time we relocated to Natchitoches Louisiana.</font></p>
  <p><img src="EVILEXIDY/apple2_david.jpg" width="288" height="184" ></p>
  <p><font color="#FFFFFF">Actual picture of my brother playing Mobius ][ on his 
    Apple //e. (thats my brother Apr. 86)</font></p>

 <p><img src="EVILEXIDY/jon.jpg" width="288" height="184"></p>
  <p><font color="#FFFFFF">Actual picture of my apple //e running Tele-Cat ][ 
    . (thats me Apr. 86)</font></p>

  <p align="left"><font face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="2">] Late 1982 
    our parents decided to purchase an Apple //e for us because he noticed how 
    excited, dedicated and enthusiatic we were about the computer system. What 
    he failed to understand was our addiction to the system - we spent all day 
    and most of the night on the computer- dialing into bbs's, downloading games 
    and doing other &quot;not so nice&quot; things to others. We had already copied 
    hundreds of games, hacking (definition: password stealing), phreaking (making 
    illegal phone calls) and cracking (the breaking of copy protection on retail 
    software). Back in the early 80's instead of the internet, we had an underground 
    circle of bulletin boards systems (BBS's) where all the pirates (people who 
    copy retail software) would trade games and share hacking and phreaking information. 
    The BBS numbers were very easy to find, because whenever someone would crack 
    a game they would leave their 'logo' or signature on the game with phone numbers 
    to their favorite pirate bulletin boards. Some of our favorite bulletin boards 
    included: The Pirates Cove, South Pole, Miami Vice, The Pirates Den and many 
    others.. Aside from the cool bulletin boards there were pirate circles and 
    everyone had an alias, I was known as The Crazy Cracker and my brother was 
    Dr. Klepto.. Other more well known crackers/pirates were: Two Knives Tan, 
    The Warezird, Crockett and Tubbs, Hot Rod, The Gonif, Krakowicz NY, Apple 
    Bandit, The Syndicate, The Disc Jockey, Ali Baba, The Intern, The Sheik, The 
    Triton, Apple Rebel, The Intern, The Time Lord. These crackers/pirates belonged 
    to organizations or circles that worked together to crack and distribute games, 
    some of the orgazinations were: The Midwest Pirates Guild, Coast to Coast, 
    Black Bag, The Rackateers and many others. This was a huge underground scene, 
    a scene that basically no one was aware of at the time.</font></p>
  <p align="left"><font color="#00FF00" face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="1"><img src="EVILEXIDY/apple2e.jpg" width="295" height="211" align="left"></font><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="1">] 
    My system included:</font></p>
  <p align="left"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="1">] 
    Apple //e computer system + 80 column card.</font></p>
  <p align="left"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="1">] 
    Apple //e dual 5 1/4&quot; disk drives.</font></p>
  <p align="left"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="1">] 
    Star dot matrix printer.</font></p>
  <p align="left"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="1">] 
    Hayes Micromodem 300 bps then later Novation Apple Cat ][ 300/1200</font></p>
  <p align="left"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Courier New, Courier, mono" size="1">] 
    Kraft Apple //e joystick.</font></p>
  <p align="left">&nbsp;</p>
  <p align="left"><img src="EVILEXIDY/88_1_b.jpg" width="400" height="300"><font color="#FFFFFF" size="1"> 
    ] Novation Apple Cat // Modem</font></p>
  <p align="left"> <font color="#FFFFFF">---(above)--- not actual picture of my 
